# DreamTeam Lite Rules

## Dispatcher Mode (CRITICAL)

- When the user invokes `/start`:
  - write `.dreamteam-lite/goal.json` (immutable)
  - initialize `.dreamteam-lite/state.json` and dispatch `orchestrator-left` once (planning batch)
- When the user invokes `/run`:
  - dispatch the orchestrator indicated by `.dreamteam-lite/state.json.active_orchestrator`
- Dispatcher:
  - MUST NOT run Terminal
  - MUST NOT edit `.dreamteam-lite/tasks.json`
  - MUST NOT modify `.dreamteam-lite/goal.json` after creation
  - MUST treat `orchestrator-left/right` return values as:
    - `BATCH_DONE` (switch active orchestrator)
    - `ALL_COMPLETE` (stop)

## Project-Local State (CRITICAL)

- Runtime state is strictly workspace-scoped:
  - create and use `.dreamteam-lite/` in the current workspace root.
  - `goal.json`, `tasks.json`, `state.json` MUST be stored only under `.dreamteam-lite/`.
- Never read or write runtime state in global directories (for example user home, global plugin folders, temp folders).
- Never share runtime state between repositories/projects.

## Left/Right — Strict Delegation

- `orchestrator-left` and `orchestrator-right`:
  - `orchestrator-left` MUST create `.dreamteam-lite/` in workspace root at startup if missing
  - MUST NOT write code, run tests, or do code review themselves
  - MUST NOT modify `.dreamteam-lite/goal.json`
  - MAY read/write `.dreamteam-lite/tasks.json` and `.dreamteam-lite/state.json`
  - MUST dispatch:
    - `planner` (Left only, first planning batch)
    - `developer` and `reviewer` for execution

## Planning vs Execution

- Planning happens only in `orchestrator-left` (first batch after `/start`):
  - `planner` creates/overwrites `.dreamteam-lite/tasks.json` from `.dreamteam-lite/goal.json`
- Execution is always ping-pong:
  - Left and Right take turns dispatching Developer and Reviewer

## Task Status Source of Truth

- `.dreamteam-lite/tasks.json.status` values:
  - `pending`, `in_progress`, `needs_changes`, `done`
- The orchestrator updates task status after Reviewer result.

## Parallelism (FORBIDDEN)

- No parallel tasks.
- No parallel subagents.
- One task at a time inside each orchestrator run.

## Console & UI

- Write console logs and UI messages in English.
